# ============================================
# INTEGRATION METHODS
# ============================================

# METHOD 1: HELIX + POWERCAB VIA L6 LINK
# - Connect: Helix L6 LINK OUT → PowerCab L6 LINK IN (110Ω XLR cable)
# - Firmware: Helix 2.80+ and PowerCab 2.0+ required
# - Result: Audio + MIDI over single cable, automatic preset sync
# - Setup: Set PowerCab MIDI channel to match Helix (default 1)
# - Best for: Simplest integration, lowest latency

# METHOD 2: HELIX + POWERCAB VIA MIDI DIN
# - Connect: Helix MIDI OUT → PowerCab MIDI IN (5-pin DIN)
# - Control: Helix Command Center sends CC/PC per snapshot
# - Example: Snapshot 1 → CC22=3 (Jarvis), Snapshot 2 → CC22=1 (Green)
# - Best for: Independent of audio routing, any modeler

# METHOD 3: THIRD-PARTY MIDI CONTROLLER
# - Compatible: Morningstar, RJM Mastermind, Disaster Area, Boss, etc.
# - Connect: Controller MIDI OUT → PowerCab MIDI IN
# - Control: Footswitches send PC (presets) or CC (parameters)
# - Best for: Dedicated PowerCab control

# METHOD 4: STEREO POWERCAB PAIR (DAISY-CHAIN)
# - Connect: Controller → PowerCab #1 IN → PowerCab #2 IN
# - Setup: Same MIDI channel, MIDI Thru enabled on #1
# - Result: Both units respond to same messages
# - L6 Link: Auto splits stereo (left → #1, right → #2)
# - Best for: Stereo rigs, dual-amp setups

# METHOD 5: TUBE AMP + POWERCAB
# - Connect: Tube amp speaker out → PowerCab INPUT 1 (Line level)
# - Mode: Speaker mode for cab simulation on XLR to FOH
# - Control: MIDI controller switches models per song
# - Result: Speaker as monitor, XLR to PA/recording
# - Best for: Hybrid tube amp + digital control

# ============================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING QUICK REFERENCE
# ============================================

# ISSUE: First preset change goes to wrong preset
# SOLUTION: Use powercab_preset_safe alias (includes initialization delay)

# ISSUE: HF driver inconsistent behavior
# SOLUTION: Send explicit CC5 values per preset, avoid expression pedals

# ISSUE: Pops/clicks when changing parameters
# SOLUTION: Use 50-100ms spacing ([+50ms] timing) between messages

# ISSUE: MIDI not responding
# SOLUTION: Check channel match, verify PC Receive enabled in Global Settings

# ISSUE: L6 Link not working
# SOLUTION: Update firmware (Helix 2.80+, PowerCab 2.0+), use 110Ω cable

# ISSUE: Volume drop via L6 Link
# SOLUTION: Adjust Helix output +10dB or PowerCab input CC1 +10dB

# ISSUE: Speaker models 6-12 missing
# SOLUTION: Update PowerCab Plus firmware to 2.0+ via Line 6 Updater

# ============================================
# MODEL COMPATIBILITY
# ============================================

# PowerCab 112 Plus: Single 12" speaker, mono, full MIDI (all features in this file)
# PowerCab 212 Plus: Dual 12" speakers, stereo, full MIDI + CC102-104 for Speaker 1
# PowerCab 112/212 (non-Plus): NO MIDI capability whatsoever (Plus required)
# PowerCab CL (112/212): Limited MIDI (only CC7, CC68-71, no Program Change)

